{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"escalatePriority"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"to"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"newPriority"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TaskPriority","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScP","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/TaskPriority"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The task which to escalate the priority of"}]}],"name":"task"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The new priority the task should continue executing on"}]}],"name":"newPriority"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"style":"warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This API should rarely be used, and instead you can rely on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"structured concurrency and implicit priority escalation which happens"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when a higher priority task awaits on a result of a lower priority task."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I.e. using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await"},{"type":"text","text":" on the target task usually is the correct way to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"escalate the target task to the current priority of the calling task,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"especially because in such setup if the waiting task gets escalated,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the waited on task would be escalated automatically as well."}]}],"name":"Warning","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The concurrency runtime is free to interpret and handle escalation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"depending on platform characteristics."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Priority escalation is propagated to child tasks of the waited-on task,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and will trigger any priority escalation handlers, if any were registered."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Escalation can only "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"increase"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the priority of a task, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"de-escalating priority is not supported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method can be called from any task or thread."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/swift/unsafecurrenttask/escalatepriority(to:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Escalate the task "},{"code":"priority","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" of the passed in task to the "},{"code":"newPriority","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"_Concurrency","title":"escalatePriority(to:)","modules":[{"relatedModules":[],"name":"Swift"}],"externalID":"s:Sct16escalatePriority2toyScP_tF","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"escalatePriority"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"to"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TaskPriority","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScP"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method"},"identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/UnsafeCurrentTask/escalatePriority(to:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com